<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?><?xml-stylesheet href="http://www.blogger.com/styles/atom.css" type="text/css"?><feed xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom' xmlns:openSearch='http://a9.com/-/spec/opensearchrss/1.0/' xmlns:blogger='http://schemas.google.com/blogger/2008' xmlns:georss='http://www.georss.org/georss' xmlns:gd="http://schemas.google.com/g/2005" xmlns:thr='http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0'><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-30128634</id><updated>2026-03-17T10:23:16.450-04:00</updated><category term="Peter Atwood"/><category term="Prybaby"/><category term="knife"/><category term="tools"/><category term="CPM154"/><category term="bottle opener"/><category term="colors"/><category term="constellation"/><category term="credit card"/><category term="drinking"/><category term="international"/><category term="jewel"/><category term="knives"/><category term="leather"/><category term="mail"/><category term="pocket knife"/><category term="postage"/><category term="prytool"/><category term="screwdriver"/><category term="shot glass"/><category term="stainless steel"/><category term="titanium"/><title type='text'>Planet Pocket Tool</title><subtitle type='html'>Adventures in Micro Manufacturing with Knife and Tool Maker Peter Atwood</subtitle><link rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#feed' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/feeds/posts/default'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/'/><link rel='hub' href='http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/'/><link rel='next' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default?start-index=26&amp;max-results=25'/><author><name>Peter Atwood</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/16246505554623368895</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='32' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiOen6fHjgWyvi3S9I_mCow2eMughd2ZfcQ0ytU2_255G3MoqnKD727X0YP4kq4wfaPIPb0bwK7kaSVsI5wQSvUSNPN1H1rNcnXOrbqaV0ewus6hFEraEGv4qpWXcVMrg/s113/*'/></author><generator version='7.00' uri='http://www.blogger.com'>Blogger</generator><openSearch:totalResults>1374</openSearch:totalResults><openSearch:startIndex>1</openSearch:startIndex><openSearch:itemsPerPage>25</openSearch:itemsPerPage><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-30128634.post-1302767634295567761</id><published>2026-03-17T09:41:00.002-04:00</published><updated>2026-03-17T10:23:16.391-04:00</updated><title type='text'>Ti ThumbNails</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;Howdy Folks, and&amp;nbsp;Happy St Patrick&#39;s Day!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Well it&#39;s a blustery day here with plenty of gusty winds and we won&#39;t get out of the 30&#39;s. But at least the sun is slated to make some appearances. We still have a few patches of snow on the ground and several giant piles left from the plow but the overall trend is definitely moving towards Spring. I expect to see crocus flowers poking up any day now and the skunk cabbage is starting to come up in the swampy areas down the road from our house.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Today I have some more Titanium ThumbNails for you. Most of these have asymmetrical grinds, stamps and anodizing. I also have a couple of plain ones left if anyone wishes to request them.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ti ThumbNails will run $55 plus shipping and the link is below. Thanks for swinging by today and I hope your week is a going well.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sold out, thank you everyone!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEimFJOPH4QRuM4mfFh8H263Sc0SbJBfZwAOVjy4ocSLzeYsXQwSIu4MfpT76F5jt0Z3fxC8YEcKKWKPHrcS8aPeE_mQBMMJQJxWHQ8CTpTjPTi5bkKSSN28bnzvljVZbXIrXTzgsm9Y-TR5y4a8GsPiNKz3uWIKvqplcyy4HSlKYEHCSWHI_ofs/s1200/111_3878.JPG&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;&quot;&gt;&lt;img border=&quot;0&quot; data-original-height=&quot;800&quot; data-original-width=&quot;1200&quot; height=&quot;213&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEimFJOPH4QRuM4mfFh8H263Sc0SbJBfZwAOVjy4ocSLzeYsXQwSIu4MfpT76F5jt0Z3fxC8YEcKKWKPHrcS8aPeE_mQBMMJQJxWHQ8CTpTjPTi5bkKSSN28bnzvljVZbXIrXTzgsm9Y-TR5y4a8GsPiNKz3uWIKvqplcyy4HSlKYEHCSWHI_ofs/s320/111_3878.JPG&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/form&gt;</content><link rel='replies' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/feeds/1302767634295567761/comments/default' title='Post Comments'/><link rel='replies' type='text/html' href='http://www.blogger.com/comment/fullpage/post/30128634/1302767634295567761' title='0 Comments'/><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/1302767634295567761'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/1302767634295567761'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/2026/03/ti-thumbnails.html' title='Ti ThumbNails'/><author><name>Peter Atwood</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/16246505554623368895</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='32' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiOen6fHjgWyvi3S9I_mCow2eMughd2ZfcQ0ytU2_255G3MoqnKD727X0YP4kq4wfaPIPb0bwK7kaSVsI5wQSvUSNPN1H1rNcnXOrbqaV0ewus6hFEraEGv4qpWXcVMrg/s113/*'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEimFJOPH4QRuM4mfFh8H263Sc0SbJBfZwAOVjy4ocSLzeYsXQwSIu4MfpT76F5jt0Z3fxC8YEcKKWKPHrcS8aPeE_mQBMMJQJxWHQ8CTpTjPTi5bkKSSN28bnzvljVZbXIrXTzgsm9Y-TR5y4a8GsPiNKz3uWIKvqplcyy4HSlKYEHCSWHI_ofs/s72-c/111_3878.JPG" height="72" width="72"/><thr:total>0</thr:total></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-30128634.post-8483650181351480631</id><published>2026-03-10T15:00:00.001-04:00</published><updated>2026-03-10T15:23:29.078-04:00</updated><title type='text'>B Stock Beads!</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;Howdy Folks,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sorry for the long radio silence lately. A nasty cold made it&#39;s rounds in our household and we are still recovering. Then suddenly last week my old work computer went on the fritz and decided to die. So it&#39;s been just a tremendous amount of fun battling viruses and then rebuilding a whole new system and recovering all of my files...not! LOL...well, thankfully all that is behind me. Now I have a blazing fast new machine, all of my data was ultimately saved and life is slowly returning to normal.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Updates: Coming up will be a brand new pocket tool design called the Pryon, probably sometime next week. I am currently in the middle of grinding more of the PryDaddy Jr tools. I have another half batch of Zr Keytons to finish and those will be coming up in couple of weeks. I have some more titanium ThumbNail tools that I am almost done with and should be coming up next. In other news, I am in the initial phase of producing some brand new fluted beads, so I am hopeful we could see a batch of them coming this spring. I also have a pile of cool new ceramic mugs that have been bisque fired, and I&#39;m hoping to get up to the studio to glaze them in the next few days. I also have several older projects that have been languishing for way too long, so hopefully I will find some shop time and get them going this spring as well.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Today I have a small batch of older Lanslide beads for you. These are titanium Minis with Racing Stripes and were among the very first batches of mini beads that I made many years ago. This group had been set aside because they were drilled slightly off center for some reason. They may have been the first couple dozen set up pieces that were turned until the program got dialed in properly. At any rate, the out of center hole is not noticeable on a lanyard and the beads are still perfectly serviceable, so it would be a shame to toss them in the bin.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;B Stock Racing Striped Beads will run $20 each plus shipping and the purchase link is below. Thanks for popping in today and hope your week is going great!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Gone in a jiffy, thank you so much!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/form&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgDAFrf8J3Tiy_y46swZW4pP821QoM1AUiPAv8kojLxs2Y06Hh_ibjNKdxUGokGYqdz5qEj2OpSrm7uLm03o7ABCB7-wgguNIBOVCB4ktm9is3i9ZwYmXkyjtd3c7fKM6UC4HUZ7JxuAVWCSBIYJCWoDcmlBNr4Qu8nHJe64QFbYOo48OknGMnZ/s1111/111_3877.JPG&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;&quot;&gt;&lt;img border=&quot;0&quot; data-original-height=&quot;714&quot; data-original-width=&quot;1111&quot; height=&quot;206&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgDAFrf8J3Tiy_y46swZW4pP821QoM1AUiPAv8kojLxs2Y06Hh_ibjNKdxUGokGYqdz5qEj2OpSrm7uLm03o7ABCB7-wgguNIBOVCB4ktm9is3i9ZwYmXkyjtd3c7fKM6UC4HUZ7JxuAVWCSBIYJCWoDcmlBNr4Qu8nHJe64QFbYOo48OknGMnZ/s320/111_3877.JPG&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/form&gt;</content><link rel='replies' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/feeds/8483650181351480631/comments/default' title='Post Comments'/><link rel='replies' type='text/html' href='http://www.blogger.com/comment/fullpage/post/30128634/8483650181351480631' title='0 Comments'/><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/8483650181351480631'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/8483650181351480631'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/2026/03/b-stock-beads.html' title='B Stock Beads!'/><author><name>Peter Atwood</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/16246505554623368895</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='32' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiOen6fHjgWyvi3S9I_mCow2eMughd2ZfcQ0ytU2_255G3MoqnKD727X0YP4kq4wfaPIPb0bwK7kaSVsI5wQSvUSNPN1H1rNcnXOrbqaV0ewus6hFEraEGv4qpWXcVMrg/s113/*'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgDAFrf8J3Tiy_y46swZW4pP821QoM1AUiPAv8kojLxs2Y06Hh_ibjNKdxUGokGYqdz5qEj2OpSrm7uLm03o7ABCB7-wgguNIBOVCB4ktm9is3i9ZwYmXkyjtd3c7fKM6UC4HUZ7JxuAVWCSBIYJCWoDcmlBNr4Qu8nHJe64QFbYOo48OknGMnZ/s72-c/111_3877.JPG" height="72" width="72"/><thr:total>0</thr:total></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-30128634.post-4864443160927940348</id><published>2026-02-20T08:53:00.001-05:00</published><updated>2026-02-20T09:03:09.486-05:00</updated><title type='text'>G2 Ghosts</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;Howdy All,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It&#39;s relatively mild this week and at least the ice is almost all off my driveway finally. It&#39;s going to be a long two months before we see some actual reasonable temps though. And today we are due for another 6 inches of snow, bleh.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I had just a dozen of these old steel G2 Ghosts laying around. They are technically B stock so expect to see some minor pitting in the steel left over from the heat treat process and lots of minor sanding marks, but they are all quite usable. None are stamped and there are no lefties...&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;B Stock G2 Ghosts will run $70 plus shipping and it&#39;s a tiny batch so one per customer please. Thanks for swinging by and I hope your weekend ahead is stellar!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Gone in a jiffy, thank you so much!&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgwnfJM7cy9gvKFuc6r0MpEhRpw9NoItTLbEvxpkzHGG0Yk9bGavhkx235zgkcPX3C4onTTFpfyJzk5WUtYe4rsbhECZs1i6dhUTRz7zyIgqYrVPwjI_SpCrZ_32oIy2V7X6IJ1fE3GfhugBAhe7DgQBCJKAIjzIA8gP-1NVezp0meHmhRpI8OH/s1200/1000000778.jpg&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;&quot;&gt;&lt;img border=&quot;0&quot; data-original-height=&quot;1200&quot; data-original-width=&quot;903&quot; height=&quot;320&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgwnfJM7cy9gvKFuc6r0MpEhRpw9NoItTLbEvxpkzHGG0Yk9bGavhkx235zgkcPX3C4onTTFpfyJzk5WUtYe4rsbhECZs1i6dhUTRz7zyIgqYrVPwjI_SpCrZ_32oIy2V7X6IJ1fE3GfhugBAhe7DgQBCJKAIjzIA8gP-1NVezp0meHmhRpI8OH/s320/1000000778.jpg&quot; width=&quot;241&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/form&gt;</content><link rel='replies' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/feeds/4864443160927940348/comments/default' title='Post Comments'/><link rel='replies' type='text/html' href='http://www.blogger.com/comment/fullpage/post/30128634/4864443160927940348' title='0 Comments'/><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/4864443160927940348'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/4864443160927940348'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/2026/02/g2-ghosts.html' title='G2 Ghosts'/><author><name>Peter Atwood</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/16246505554623368895</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='32' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiOen6fHjgWyvi3S9I_mCow2eMughd2ZfcQ0ytU2_255G3MoqnKD727X0YP4kq4wfaPIPb0bwK7kaSVsI5wQSvUSNPN1H1rNcnXOrbqaV0ewus6hFEraEGv4qpWXcVMrg/s113/*'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgwnfJM7cy9gvKFuc6r0MpEhRpw9NoItTLbEvxpkzHGG0Yk9bGavhkx235zgkcPX3C4onTTFpfyJzk5WUtYe4rsbhECZs1i6dhUTRz7zyIgqYrVPwjI_SpCrZ_32oIy2V7X6IJ1fE3GfhugBAhe7DgQBCJKAIjzIA8gP-1NVezp0meHmhRpI8OH/s72-c/1000000778.jpg" height="72" width="72"/><thr:total>0</thr:total></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-30128634.post-1540775320780471061</id><published>2026-02-12T10:13:00.002-05:00</published><updated>2026-02-12T11:01:25.162-05:00</updated><title type='text'>Area 51 Zirconium E115s</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;Hello Folks,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Well, after many weeks of unbelievably cold temperatures this winter, Mother Nature has finally granted us a reprieve! We are going to reach 30 degrees today, and that is just fantastic. I think I might put a blanket out on the snow and do some sunbathing, hehe. And we are going to be seeing 40&#39;s for the next few days, so that will be quite welcome indeed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I&#39;ve been busy in the shop grinding tools and making a few mugs. Several new drawings have been finalized as well, so there will be some nice goodies coming up in the next few weeks and months.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Today I have a couple dozen fancy E115 tools for you. This is the tail end of the Zirconium Wroid batch and on these I have elected to give them a wide variety of A51 extra grinds and stamps. No lefties remain unfortunately and no plain ones either, but they do have that new glassy, burnished finish that the recent Zr Keytons had.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A51 Zirconium E115 Wroids will run $90 plus shipping and the link is below. Thanks for popping in today and hope your upcoming weekend is a warm one.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;All gone, thank you so much! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEif7EyelM7hWfEnjXPLFbACPSkDUMAM3FgLd_l5x_QWlLxxqMMyFliTpBvxPRUKEWZDmvn_ZL9yEOkiy5eEv_Hbj7h7TyWPE8AYMY3zB34Q8qgGkSNi3ifhhT2jXveZT5-ed0pPb1VHefGF4RsqUPkLhbNDVPzTkuF6UzZNezxMYCRGyv42Qxm5/s879/e115.jpg&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;&quot;&gt;&lt;img border=&quot;0&quot; data-original-height=&quot;879&quot; data-original-width=&quot;674&quot; height=&quot;320&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEif7EyelM7hWfEnjXPLFbACPSkDUMAM3FgLd_l5x_QWlLxxqMMyFliTpBvxPRUKEWZDmvn_ZL9yEOkiy5eEv_Hbj7h7TyWPE8AYMY3zB34Q8qgGkSNi3ifhhT2jXveZT5-ed0pPb1VHefGF4RsqUPkLhbNDVPzTkuF6UzZNezxMYCRGyv42Qxm5/s320/e115.jpg&quot; width=&quot;245&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/form&gt;</content><link rel='replies' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/feeds/1540775320780471061/comments/default' title='Post Comments'/><link rel='replies' type='text/html' href='http://www.blogger.com/comment/fullpage/post/30128634/1540775320780471061' title='0 Comments'/><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/1540775320780471061'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/1540775320780471061'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/2026/02/area-51-zirconium-e115s.html' title='Area 51 Zirconium E115s'/><author><name>Peter Atwood</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/16246505554623368895</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='32' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiOen6fHjgWyvi3S9I_mCow2eMughd2ZfcQ0ytU2_255G3MoqnKD727X0YP4kq4wfaPIPb0bwK7kaSVsI5wQSvUSNPN1H1rNcnXOrbqaV0ewus6hFEraEGv4qpWXcVMrg/s113/*'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEif7EyelM7hWfEnjXPLFbACPSkDUMAM3FgLd_l5x_QWlLxxqMMyFliTpBvxPRUKEWZDmvn_ZL9yEOkiy5eEv_Hbj7h7TyWPE8AYMY3zB34Q8qgGkSNi3ifhhT2jXveZT5-ed0pPb1VHefGF4RsqUPkLhbNDVPzTkuF6UzZNezxMYCRGyv42Qxm5/s72-c/e115.jpg" height="72" width="72"/><thr:total>0</thr:total></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-30128634.post-3159065590569895811</id><published>2026-01-28T12:17:00.001-05:00</published><updated>2026-01-28T14:45:28.156-05:00</updated><title type='text'>Zirconium Keytons</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;Howdy Folks!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Brrr...it&#39;s another freezing cold day here in New England. I reckon we got somewhere between 15-18 inches of snow over the weekend, but it&#39;s hard to say exactly because the snow is so powdery and drifty that it makes measuring very difficult. And the below zero degree and single digit temperatures that accompanied it have been quite miserable. We have a few more days of this and then we should get a little bit of a reprieve, although when 30F feels tropical you know you&#39;ve been through the ringer!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Today I have the first wave of Zirconium Keytons for you. These came out with a very nice glassy looking finish that I just started experimenting with. They feature my usual wide range of stamps, although I did leave a couple without stamps for anyone who wishes to request them. I also have a couple of lefties.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Zirconium Keytons will run $85 plus shipping and the link is below. Thanks for swinging by and I hope you&#39;re staying warm out there!&lt;/p&gt;Sold out for now, thank you so much!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEinVhKg3mJB_jAmSHb6KEZXjLqxYgnjLrnD-c3KNFYx-GD4czFVhTRLTGE6bnxwTHSTpNy1GhtwuhD1ZXgWNt04YnpcSMeB3yV77eOnjTr3oBG580S2NUCiVi_GJhTZfJ84dmyHIZPGjUfnZtJRLvcD0sIsBJHzpiEOqk6RApyPjz-BvunZTP7O/s1200/111_3830.JPG&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;&quot;&gt;&lt;img border=&quot;0&quot; data-original-height=&quot;800&quot; data-original-width=&quot;1200&quot; height=&quot;213&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEinVhKg3mJB_jAmSHb6KEZXjLqxYgnjLrnD-c3KNFYx-GD4czFVhTRLTGE6bnxwTHSTpNy1GhtwuhD1ZXgWNt04YnpcSMeB3yV77eOnjTr3oBG580S2NUCiVi_GJhTZfJ84dmyHIZPGjUfnZtJRLvcD0sIsBJHzpiEOqk6RApyPjz-BvunZTP7O/s320/111_3830.JPG&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/form&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/form&gt;</content><link rel='replies' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/feeds/3159065590569895811/comments/default' title='Post Comments'/><link rel='replies' type='text/html' href='http://www.blogger.com/comment/fullpage/post/30128634/3159065590569895811' title='0 Comments'/><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/3159065590569895811'/><link rel='self' type='application/ato