534807</id><published>2026-01-06T10:14:00.002-05:00</published><updated>2026-01-06T17:44:17.875-05:00</updated><title type='text'>Happy New Year!</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;Howdy Folks, and a Happy 2026 to you! I hope your holiday season was relaxing and that you got some time to kick back. Thank you so much for your loyal support for 2025, it was very much appreciated, and I&#39;m very excited for what will be coming in this year ahead.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It was unfortunate that much of what I had planned for the pre holiday season last year was so slow to get going that much of it came back to me from heat treat either just before or right after Christmas. However, it leaves me in great shape for this winter and I now have oodles of things either finished or close to done. Some very fun stuff is coming up. :)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Today, fresh back from S&amp;amp;W heat treat, I have the Steel Skeletaur Tools for you. Quality steels are getting harder to source because of the shut down of Crucible, and like everything else they keep climbing in price. So these tools are made from CPM 20CV which was what was available when I cut them last summer. This new-to-me material was a little more difficult to grind and it Rockwells out at 59, so it is going to be excellent for durability. Most of the Skeletaurs are stamped but I do have a handful that are plain. There are also a half dozen lefties for anyone who wishes to email me for them.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Steel Skeletaurs will be $80 plus shipping and the link is below. Thanks for swinging by this week, and I hope your 2026 is getting off to a great start!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;All gone for now, thank you again! &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleuser