 a later date.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Well today I have just a little batch for you. These are the remaining Titanium Bermuda Beads from a few years back. They are anodized a wide range of colors and make a nice little &quot;stacker&quot; piece to go with other beads on a lanyard.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ti Bermuda Beads will run $30 plus shipping and the link is below. Thanks once again for slipping by, and I hope your week is shaping up to be a good one.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;All gone, thank you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjPP8IKS0FGK20NWkXhOXyq6ZmLndQqcZm-B-1dUFDM322Kq9hqK1zI585kwxkW5lphgRI1dYZvEVYBA6CdXxNF3PeT9iw4Avt9vRi9oZzDB8Ct3xFCaqbxAe7u2YIKzR5clpH63ppC23cu4Z-oo6FYwYuAoLbeQaYXYiByRIZEpScFZ6WjCBl3/s1200/111_3804.JPG&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;&quot;&gt;&lt;img border=&quot;0&quot; data-original-height=&quot;800&quot; data-original-width=&quot;1200&quot; height=&quot;213&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjPP8IKS0FGK20NWkXhOXyq6ZmLndQqcZm-B-1dUFDM322Kq9hqK1zI585kwxkW5lphgRI1dYZvEVYBA6CdXxNF3PeT9iw4Avt9vRi9oZzDB8Ct3xFCaqbxAe7u2YIKzR5clpH63ppC23cu4Z-oo6FYwYuAoLbeQaYXYiByRIZEpScFZ6WjCBl3/s320/111_3804.JPG&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/form&gt;</content><link rel='replies' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/feeds/4743715260553863291/comments/default' title='Post Comments'/><link rel='replies' type='text/html' href='http://www.blogger.com/comment/fullpage/post/30128634/4743715260553863291' title='0 Comments'/><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/4743715260553863291'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/30128634/posts/default/4743715260553863291'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://atwoodknives.blogspot.com/2025/11/bermuda-beads.html' title='Bermuda Beads'/><author><name>Peter Atwood</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/16246505554623368895</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='32' height='32' src='//blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiOen6fHjgWyvi3S9I_mCow2eMughd2ZfcQ0ytU2_255G3MoqnKD727X0YP4kq4wfaPIPb0bwK7kaSVsI5wQSvUSNPN1H1rNcnXOrbqaV0ewus6hFEraEGv4qpWXcVMrg/s113/*'/></author><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjPP8IKS0FGK20NWkXhOXyq6ZmLndQqcZm-B-1dUFDM322Kq9hqK1zI585kwxkW5lphgRI1dYZvEVYBA6CdXxNF3PeT9iw4Avt9vRi9oZzDB8Ct3xFCaqbxAe7u2YIKzR5clpH63ppC23cu4Z-oo6FYwYuAoLbeQaYXYiByRIZEpScFZ6WjCBl3/s72-c/111_3804.JPG" height="72" width="72"/><thr:total>0</thr:total></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-30128634.post-7386892441181422422</id><published>2025-11-17T09:33:00.004-05:00</published><updated>2025-11-17T10:11:11.448-05:00</updated><title type='text'>Zirconium Mini Superbugs!</title><content type='html'>&lt;p&gt;Good morning, and a Happy Monday to you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It&#39;s bright out there this morning, a bit cloudy but there&#39;s supposed to be quite a lot of sun today. It&#39;s quite chilly though with highs only about 40f predicted, and very windy later this morning. So it is going to be cold out there today.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I spent much of the weekend going through odds and ends in the shop and on the shelves. Some stuff was already finished and other pieces needed further processing. My main tumbler needs some maintenance as it is limping along and that is something I will need to tackle later this week. But for now I have gathered up some small groups of items for you and that will take me through for a few days.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Today I have a handful of Zirconium Mini Superbug Tools for you. I made these little bit caddy tools a few years ago. They have a wide variety of stamps on them and feature a cap lifter and captive bit system. The torch blackened surface is extremely hard and will stay nice for years of hostile pocket wear. I ran out of Phillips screwdriver tips so some of these will have T-10 Torx bits as I had a few dozen lying around. But of course you can use any 1 inch bit you want in them. A handy little item that is easy to carry. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Zirconium Mini Superbug Tools will run $65 plus shipping and the link is below. Thanks for coming by today and have a great week.&lt;/p&gt;Sold out, thanks very much!&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgSBtk44OH9_i-9blXYwuJQegBuZaOx681iR18Pi5p_8x_ANkItmqvOeX2lEDC9jTxHoYF8cDjDGPC9KIa800c-BCGNzPK7Nmk_iGAnlEQ-eyzYsoIXQWFBEfyxIE5UTEC4eQXcNvzNZamO1P3YDhXG0MQnJG2XUKVlx2vu51LT63dfTalsQcIC/s4512/111_3800.JPG&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;&quot;&gt;&lt;img border=&quot;0&quot; data-original-height=&quot;3008&quot; data-original-width=&quot;4512&quot; height=&quot;213&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgSBtk44OH9_i-9blXYwuJQegBuZaOx681iR18Pi5p_8x_ANkItmqvOeX2lEDC9jTxHoYF8cDjDGPC9KIa800c-BCGNzPK7Nmk_iGAnlEQ-eyzYsoIXQWFBEfyxIE5UTEC4eQXcNvzNZamO1P3YDhXG0MQnJG2XUKVlx2vu51LT63dfTalsQcIC/s320/111_3800.JPG&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/form&gt;&lt;form action=&quot;https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr&quot; method=&quot;post&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/form&gt;</content><